## Erlang VM args for the release. The node name, distribution mode, and cookie are set
## from the environment (RELEASE_NODE / RELEASE_DISTRIBUTION / RELEASE_COOKIE; see
## rel/env.sh.eex), so they are intentionally NOT hard-coded here.

## Pin the Erlang distribution listen ports to a small fixed range so the VPC firewall
## can allow exactly these (plus epmd on 4369) between relay instances and nothing else.
-kernel inet_dist_listen_min 9100 inet_dist_listen_max 9105
